definitions.definition: Any of a group of various types of grass or its grains used as food, widely cultivated in the developing world.
( specifically ) Common millet , in particular of species Panicum miliaceum .

main_definition: Any of a group of various types of grass or its grains used as food, widely cultivated in the developing world.
secondary_definitions: ( specifically ) Common millet , in particular of species Panicum miliaceum .

definitions.definition: A semi-autonomous confessional community under the Ottoman Empire, especially a non-Muslim one.

main_definition: ( historical ) A semi-autonomous confessional community under the Ottoman Empire, especially a non-Muslim one. [from 19th c.]
